OL,6,FAs well as a third of people looking
OL,7,Fto reduce their screen time, three
OL,8,Fquarters said they were hoping to
OL,9,Fimprove their mental health ` with a
OL,10,Ffurther two thirds (65%) wanting to
OL,11,Fsleep better.
OL,13,FHalf of those polled (49%) admitted to
OL,14,Fprevious unsuccessful attempts to
OL,15,Freduce screen time.
OL,17,FVirgin Media O2 said this explained
OL,18,Frecord levels of data consumption and
OL,19,Fan overall uptick of 8.1% in broadband
OL,20,Fusage on its network last year.
